
Before starting, make sure you have the ANTLR aliases:
alias antlr4='java -jar /usr/local/lib/antlr-4.7.2-complete.jar'
alias grun='java org.antlr.v4.gui.TestRig'


JAVA:

To use the Region grammar for testing in java use:

antlr4 Region.g4 -o Region_javatest

The -o is optional output directory (default is cwd), which can help keep the grammar directory clean.

Inside the output directory the java files can be compiled:

cd Region_javatest
javac *.java

And then the default test can be launched:

grun Region region ../10_bigup.inp -gui

The syntax is:

grun [GRAMMAR_NAME] [RULE] [TESTFILE] -gui 


PYTHON:

To generate or refresh the grammar files for python use:

antlr4 -Dlanguage=Python2 -visitor -no-listener Region.g4